   <taskbody>
      <prereq class="- topic/section task/prereq ">
         <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Mail merge is configured for the selected form. <p product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/p ">For additional information, refer to <xref href="../../Library_Management/Standard_Library_Catalogs/Notifications/ConfigMailMerge.dita"
                        class="- topic/xref ">Configuring Mail Merge</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">You are invited to the project and provided with the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Edit</uicontrol> permission.</li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can attach a mail merge document to a specific record of a form.</context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the required list page of a form, select a record for which the notification has to be attached. </cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mail Merge</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Merge and Attach</uicontrol>. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Merge and Attach</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">From the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Mail Merge Configuration</uicontrol> drop-down list, select the required configuration. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">Available options are all the configurations associated with the form. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For additional information, refer to <xref href="../../Library_Management/Standard_Library_Catalogs/Notifications/ConfigMailMerge.dita"
                        class="- topic/xref ">Configuring Mail Merge</xref>.</ph>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To convert the mail merge document to PDF, select the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Convert to PDF</uicontrol> check box. If the check box is cleared, then the mail merge document is attached in the Word format. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note class="- topic/note "> If the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Convert to PDF</uicontrol> check box is selected at the time when the mail merge is configured, then this check box is selected. Clear the check box to attach the mail merge document in PDF format.</note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Attach</uicontrol>. </cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The mail merge document is attached to the record and available in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ATTACHMENTS</uicontrol> section of the record.</info>
         </step>
      </steps>
